The key insight from the natural language proof is:
1. For any vertex v in H := G - X, we have ν(H - v) = ν(H) (by maximality of X)
2. This implies every component C of H is odd and has ν(C) = (|C| - 1)/2
3. Therefore H has a matching leaving exactly one vertex per component unmatched
4. This gives ν(H) = (|V(H)| - odd(H))/2

